==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Euphuist
<hw>Eu"phu*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who affects excessive
refinement and elegance of language; -- applied esp. to a class of
writers, in the age of Elizabeth, whose productions are marked by
affected conceits and high-flown diction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Euphuistic</ent>⟦br⟧
